Of this great House, & those that henceforth shall
(As that will last) foreuer sing the same,
But, if on me, my garland iustly fall,
I iustly owe my Musique to this name.
   For he vnlawfully vsurps the Bayes
   That has not sung in Noble Norreys prayse.
 
                              .8.
In playne (my honour’d Lord) I was not borne
Audacious vowes, or forraigne legs to vse,
Nature denyed my outside to adorne,
And I, of art to learrne outsides refuse.
Yet haueing of them both, enough to scorne
Silence, & vulgar prayse, this humble Muse
   And her meane favourite, at your Command
   Chose in this kinde, to kisse your noble hand.

Of this great House, & those that henceforth shall

(As that will last) foreuer sing the same,

But, if on me, my garland iustly fall,

I iustly owe my Musique to this name.

   For he vnlawfully vsurps the Bayes

   That has not sung in Noble Norreys prayse.

 

                              .8.

In playne (my honour’d Lord) I was not borne

Audacious vowes, or forraigne legs to vse,

Nature denyed my outside to adorne,

And I, of art to learrne outsides refuse.

Yet haueing of them both, enough to scorne

Silence, & vulgar prayse, this humble Muse

   And her meane favourite, at your Command

   Chose in this kinde, to kisse your noble hand.
